data.text:
Tropical Storm #Nestor reminding everyone here in Mexico Beach, Florida of what happened nearly exactly one year ago, when Hurricane Michael roared ashore as a category 5 hurricane. 

How folks are getting ready for the storm’s arrival tonight on @NBCNightlyNews. https://t.co/Z3FVFhgpmP

Before the hurricane could make a pass about 30 ft deep, it had to level dunes that were some 30 ft tall. The appearance of the water after the storm passed was stunning though & in the following weeks, it appeared as if the bay itself looked more beautiful...

One year ago today, Hurricane Michael left Mexico Beach, Florida in ruins. I had never heard of it before that day. Now it’s become a place I’ll never forget. So glad to be here for the anniversary event. It’s still rough but getting better every day. #mexicobeachstrong @spann https://t.co/Kwd5TUFQEe

After initially answering the question, he turns the camera on himself & gets real concerning how dangerous it could be to stay on #CapeSanBlas during the hurricane. He was correct about the storm surge because it was so powerful that the state park was severed into 3 parts.

entity.name: Clarence
entity.description: Clarence is a spirited boy who sees the best in everything. His unique perspective on life transforms even a mundane situation into one that is interesting or fun. Epic dirt fights, awkward crushes and secret tree forts are all par for the course for the youngster, who shares his experiences with his family and friends. That group includes his best friends, scrappy Sumo and cautious Jeff, patient mom Mary, and her laid-back boyfriend, Chad. Clarence's adventures should be familiar to many people from their own childhoods, but he takes them to the limit.
